review_blob:
Enjoyed one of these winter lagers at the Pearl Street Pub with 3 giant pieces of white fish and delicious bacon stuffed balls.

---Rated via Beer Buddy

Thought this was a tasty IPA for not being an IPA drinker. A beer I would recoomend however to other IPA drinkers, seeing that is it a benchmark for the beer judge certification program. Had a sample of this at the Corridor Beer Fest in Iowa.

Tasted this stout at the Corridor Beerfest in Cedar Rapids. Smooth tasting with a bit of a bite. A beer I would drink again.

---Rated via Beer Buddy
beer_name: Left Coast Voo Doo American Stout

review_blob:
Tripel are one of my favorite styles. This beer lives up to its name, but not as smooth and a little to much banana taste. Enjoyed a bottle at Mastro's in Phoenix. Not worth the 16 I paid, but worth a try if you can find it cheaper.

---Rated via Beer Buddy

The big wave was not a bad golden ale, but I have had better. Enjoyed this with a pile of BBQ from Rudy's in Phoenix. It is a fun bottle and name, but don't always judge a beer by its label.

---Rated via Beer Buddy

Tasted this at Rudy's in Phoenix while enjoying some delicious Texas BBQ. Great crisp flavor like a cider, but heavier like an ale. Perfect beer to go with the spicy flavor of the BBQ.

---Rated via Beer Buddy

My brother bought a 750ml bottle of this to share. Enjoyed a glass with him and a handful of my closest friends. You could really get the wine barrel taste as you do with most Jolly Pumpkin. I could drink the whole bottle, but it is to sweet to enjoy much more than that in may opinion.

My brother bought a 750ml bottle of this to share. Enjoyed a glass with him and a handful of my closest friends. We all thought it very smooth ale with good taste. Would be interesting in trying the Dubbel or Tripel.

Had this beer at lunch. It was alright, and reminded me of a Heineken. A beer  light enough I could get drunk on, but not anything special. Worth a buy, just because the bottle is awesome.

---Rated via Beer Buddy

Looks and taste as you would expect a lager. However it did have a bit more flavor than a typical budlight, just nothing I enjoyed. Probably a good starter for someone wanting to get into drinking craft beers. Not something I would try again.

I really enjoyed this beer. It tasted just as good as it looks and would recommend it to anyone wanting a black IPA on a cold winters day. Enjoyed this with a group of friends celebrating another successful fantasy football season.

At first I thought this was going to be a great beer from initial taste. But as I kept drinking, I kept thinking how more and more it tasted like dirt. Something I would not jump at trying again. Had this beer at the Coralville Brrfest.
I was not a big fan of this beer. Maybe it was to early to start thinking Munich Helles because this did not work in my opinion. I tasted this beer at a beer tasting event, Brrfest, in Coralville, IA
This beer was not aschocolate smoothie tasting as it sounded. Still a decent brew. I enjoyed this beer at a beer tasting event, Brrfest, in Coralville, IA
This does shine just as the deScription notes. A great tasting lager, that is worth the wait. A beer I would drink again. I enjoyed this beer at a beer tasting event, Brrfest, in Coralville, IA

A decent tasting oatmeal stout. Something I would try again, and I am not a big stout drinker. However it is not one of my favorites. Enjoyed this beer at a beer tasting event, Brrfest, in Coralville, IA

Could really taste the sourness of the beer. I was not a fan of the sour ale, nor the disapointement learning it did not contain real cherries but decided to give it a try anyway. I tasted this beer at a beer tasting event, Brrfest, in Coralville, IA

A unique beer that is a must try for anyone who likes heat. It reminded me of a light beer I had with a few drops of Cayenne Pepper Extract. Enjoyed this beer at a beer tasting event, Brrfest, in Coralville, IA

Enjoyed this for breakfast before Brrfest. It went well with the breakfast casserole, but it was not something I would drink more than 8-12 ounces in one sitting. It had a very rich maple taste, with a smokey finish. If you like unique flavors, then you should give it a try.
beer_name: Rogue Voodoo Doughnut Bacon Maple Ale

review_blob: Enjoyed this beer at a beer tasting event, Brrfest, in Coralville, IA.  Could not taste the meat drippings, but it was pretty good. Did have a sweet and tart taste. Definitely worth a try.
Enjoyed this beer at a beer tasting event, Brrfest, in Coralville, IA. A decent oatmeal stout, but not one of my favorites. Confluence has much better beer to try.
Tasted this at the backpocket brewery prior to attending Brrfest. It was very smooth with a clean after taste. A beer I would get again.

Enjoyed this beer as part of a sampler pack at the Nebraska Brewing Company with Family. Not a bad brew. Good color and a average taste. They have better beers I would drink at Nebraska Brewing. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy

Enjoyed this beer as part of a sampler pack at the Nebraska Brewing Company with Family. I don't really care for IPAs, and this one did not change my mind. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy

Enjoyed this beer as part of a sampler pack at the Nebraska Brewing Company with Family. I am not a huge hop head, but I enjoy a good hoppy beer now and again. This was one of the best I have tasted. Definitely recommend trying.

---Rated via Beer Buddy

Enjoyed this beer as part of a sampler pack at the Nebraska Brewing Company with Family. It had a good taste, worth a try if you enjoy that style of beer.

---Rated via Beer Buddy

Exactly how described, an ale to bring over the lager drinkers. A very light beer with a slight taste. A good starter for those bud light and miller fans. I enjoyed this as the first beer in sampler of beers along with a Po Boy Wrap for lunch at the Nebraska Brewing Company Restaurant with Family.

---Rated via Beer Buddy

Enjoyed this as part of a sampler of beers along with a Po Boy Wrap for lunch at the Nebraska Brewing Company Restaurant with Family. A definite German wheat. Great aroma, not bad flavor. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy

Enjoyed this as part of a sampler of beers along with a Po Boy Wrap for lunch at the Nebraska Brewing Company Restaurant with Family. This was not a bad wheat, very traditional flavors. Would recommend a try if you like Wheat Beers.

---Rated via Beer Buddy

Enjoyed a couple of these brew on New Year's Eve 2012. Not a bad brew, but nothing remarkable about the beer. The coolest part about the beer is the name. Dead Guy ale just sounds cool. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy

Enjoyed this delicous IPA with my Family and a bowl of Chili at dinner the day after Christmas. It had a great flavor and very satisfying after taste. Like everyone else has said, this is the best IPA I have ever tried, and I dont like IPAs all that much.

Enjoyed this out of a bottle on Christmas Eve with the family. Very rich flavor, and enjoyed the spiced after taste. Thankful that my brother shared his six pack.

---Rated via Beer Buddy

A beer with a great name that I had to try while dining with a few friends. A strong IPA, with a decent finish. I really tasted the floral sweetness and tropical favors as described. Worth a try if you like IPA, but it wont be making my list of favorites.

Enjoyed this on Tap out at a local resturant with a few friends. Being 12% it had a very strong powerful almost wine flavor. It went great with the 1lb Chicago Ribeye. I would recommend trying it with your favorite steak.

Had this beer in the Shires rest outside of Hobbiton in New Zealand. I was told it was originally brewed for The Lord of the Rings crew so they could film the party scene and not get drunk. I thought it was not bad, something I could drink quite a few of one night. Worth a 12 pack.

Enjoyed a pull of this at Pub n Grub in Taupo, New Zealand near the lake. Not a bad brew to enjoy with Dinner, but nothing special either. A typically Lager, but right up there with the Bud Selects of the world.
Tried this at the brewery in New Zealand, one of there seasonal brews. A unique flavor of beer. Could really taste the chilis. Best Mexican style beer I have ever tried.
The best of a group of a sample palette at the brewery in New Zealand. A very smooth and creamy dark style brew. Highly recommended to try if you try any.

A tasty beer I enjoyed along with with three others in a sample palette at the brewery in New Zealand. A great hop beer and I found it had a great rich malt flavor as deScription. A beer I would buy a six pack of and enjoy one evening.

A beer I enjoyed in a sample palette at the brewery in New Zealand. It was alright, probably least favorite out of the group. I could taste the chocolate, but not a beer for me. Worth a try however if you like Brown Ale.

A tasty beer I enjoyed along with with three others in a sample palette at the brewery in New Zealand. Also the first of five samples that day. Nothing special, but something I could drink it all night easily.

Had this beer at the Cedar Rapids Farmers Market. It was a hot day, so I was a little wary trying such a dark beer. However I was rewarded with a very smooth creamy taste with a hint of chocolate. Very good, would purchase more.
Obviously this a mass produced light beer with little flavor and poor appearance. But for a long day of drinking while moving someone into a new place followed by a bonfire, this will do the trick.
This beer gets a perfect score for me. The perfect blend of beer and bourbon makes this a easy to drink with a smooth finish. I have not had anything better.
I was first drawn in by the name, then the deScription. This is a great beer with smooth tast that I love to have in dark beers. Be carful though, the 9% alcohol level can creep up on you fast.

A pretty good ale, and not just because its from Ireland. I agree, that is it very rich and therefore I find it more of a dinner beer, having a handful, but not something to drink all night if you are intending to party animal house style.

I found this an average beer. I am starting to feel like all Sam Adams has a certain taste to it, that you can tell if you are drinking any one of their flavors. I found there is much better summer ales out there, but could settle on this if that is all that was offered.

Had this beer at a local pub with a batch of chicken wings. It had a great smooth flavor, little to no bitterness that I could taste. Like most people said it ours Brown, just like the name, Brown Ale. Overall I would have another (which I did).
The only thing this beer has going for it is a cool blue bottle. Past that it almost tasted like watered down bud light with an attempt at lemonade flavor. I would stick with regular Bud Light.

I had this on tap at a local resturant. Once I saw that is was Belguim Trippel I had to try it. Great flavor with a nice sweet finish, making it hard to beleive has a 11% alcohol rating. Worth every penny.
